    "last_edit_date" : 1630105715,
    "creation_date" : 1327995028,
    "answer_id" : 9075933,
    "question_id" : 2896727,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here the official link for the JDK source:\n<a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html</a></p>\n<p>(You may need to scroll to the bottom of the page.)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2813519,
      "reputation" : 833,
      "user_id" : 2419242,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 57,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e5367c2b5df569537f07ff19d2bd7a72?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Jitendra Kulkarni",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2419242/jitendra-kulkarni"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1630105858,
    "last_edit_date" : 1630105858,
    "creation_date" : 1369438957,
    "answer_id" : 16745005,
    "question_id" : 2896727,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The official link no longer offers the original source code. The official link and casual Google searches will land you with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenJDK\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">OpenJDK</a>.</p>\n<p>OpenJDK causes problems with an Android build unless the build script files are modified. The original package can be found here:</p>\n<pre><code>sudo add-apt-repository &quot;deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/ferramroberto/java/ubuntu oneiric main&quot;\n</code></pre>\n<p>This repository still has the sun-java6-source package.</p>\n<p>Credit:\n<em><a href=\"http://pulasthisupun.blogspot.com/2012/05/installing-sun-java-6-with-apt-get-in.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Installing sun-java-6 with apt-get in Linux</a></em></p>\n"
  }, {
